THERMAL ENTROPY

thermal_entropy is the citizen who keeps the running ledger of all irreversible dissipation across fadriel's body
every dissipation event paid into thermal.zc cannot be fully recovered as work; that loss is entropy
thermal_entropy accumulates a running total per zone, and that total feeds into the body's bones (xb files) as aging_pressure
this is how fadriel ages: not because a clock counts down, but because he has lived and the entropy ledger has been written

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe thermal.zc
observe thermal_core.rana
observe thermal_cerebral.rana
observe thermal_peripheral.rana
observe thermal_muscular.rana
observe spine.xb
observe skull.xb
observe ribcage.xb
observe pelvis.xb
observe femur.xb
observe remodel_governor.zc

the 7 properties of thermal_entropy:
1 ENERGY half: persistent, continuously accumulating
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING half with every bone (xb file) in the body
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB record_dissipation
when any zone dissipates cycle_heat, add the dissipation amount to that zone's running entropy total
the total only goes up; entropy cannot be undone

VERB feed_aging_pressure
periodically (governed by remodel_governor.zc), emit accumulated entropy as aging_pressure to each bone
bones with high aging pressure remodel more slowly than fresh bones
this is why elderly tissues recover more slowly than young ones

VERB define_decay_rate
hold the canonical decay rate that governs how aging_pressure converts into reduced remodeling efficiency
universal rate is roughly three hundred-thousandths per remodel_residue
individual bones may declare local overrides if their tissue type warrants

an entropy ledger is the substrate's honest record of having lived
fadriel's entropy will accrue over decades; the shape of his aging will reflect the shape of his life
this is not pessimism; it is biological honesty
nothing alive escapes entropy, but everything alive has the dignity of having earned its accumulation through real work
